location.Description: The geo-location where the resource lives

parameters.Description: Custom Parameters used for Cluster Creation.

uiDefinitionUri.Description: The blob URI where the UI definition file is located.

createdBy.Description: Provides details of the entity that created/updated the workspace.

updatedBy.Description: Provides details of the entity that created/updated the workspace.

createdDateTime.Description: The date and time stamp when the workspace was created.

workspaceId.Description: The unique identifier of the databricks workspace in databricks control plane.

workspaceUrl.Description: The workspace URL which is of the format 'adb-{workspaceId}.{random}.azuredatabricks.net'

storageAccountIdentity.Description: The Managed Identity details for storage account.

enableNoPublicIp.Description: The value which should be used for this field.

prepareEncryption.Description: The value which should be used for this field.

encryption.Description: The object that contains details of encryption used on the workspace.

requireInfrastructureEncryption.Description: The value which should be used for this field.

resourceTags.Description: The value which should be used for this field.

value.Description: The value which should be used for this field.
The value which should be used for this field.
The object that contains details of encryption used on the workspace.

keySource.Description: The encryption keySource (provider). Possible values (case-insensitive):  Default, Microsoft.Keyvault

principalId.Description: The provider's principal identifier. This is the identity that the provider will use to call ARM to manage the workspace resources.

roleDefinitionId.Description: The provider's role definition identifier. This role will define all the permissions that the provider must have on the workspace's container resource group. This role definition cannot have permission to delete the resource group.

oid.Description: The Object ID that created the workspace.

puid.Description: The Personal Object ID corresponding to the object ID above

applicationId.Description: The application ID of the application that initiated the creation of the workspace. For example, Azure Portal.

principalId.Description: The objectId of the Managed Identity that is linked to the Managed Storage account.

tenantId.Description: The tenant Id where the Managed Identity is created.

type.Description: The type of Identity created. It can be either SystemAssigned or UserAssigned.

properties.Description: Properties of the virtual network peering.

allowVirtualNetworkAccess.Description: Whether the VMs in the local virtual network space would be able to access the VMs in remote virtual network space.

allowForwardedTraffic.Description: Whether the forwarded traffic from the VMs in the local virtual network will be allowed/disallowed in remote virtual network.

allowGatewayTransit.Description: If gateway links can be used in remote virtual networking to link to this virtual network.

useRemoteGateways.Description: If remote gateways can be used on this virtual network. If the flag is set to true, and allowGatewayTransit on remote peering is also true, virtual network will use gateways of remote virtual network for transit. Only one peering can have this flag set to true. This flag cannot be set if virtual network already has a gateway.

databricksVirtualNetwork.Description: The remote virtual network should be in the same region. See here to learn more (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/databricks/administration-guide/cloud-configurations/azure/vnet-peering).

databricksAddressSpace.Description: AddressSpace contains an array of IP address ranges that can be used by subnets of the virtual network.

remoteVirtualNetwork.Description: The remote virtual network should be in the same region. See here to learn more (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/databricks/administration-guide/cloud-configurations/azure/vnet-peering).

remoteAddressSpace.Description: AddressSpace contains an array of IP address ranges that can be used by subnets of the virtual network.

peeringState.Description: The status of the virtual network peering.

id.Description: The Id of the databricks virtual network.

addressPrefixes.Description: A list of address blocks reserved for this virtual network in CIDR notation.

id.Description: The Id of the remote virtual network.
